
[1]turmalin

   TUR'MALIN, n. [probably a corruption of tournamal, a name given to this
   stone in Ceylon.] In mineralogy, a silicious stone, sometimes used as a
   gem by jewelers, remarkable for exhibiting electricity by heat or
   friction. It occurs in long prisms deeply striated. Its fracture is
   conchoidal, and its internal luster vitreous.

   Turmalin is considered as a variety of shorl.
